    <p>Cold brew mixes better than hot coffee for whey. If you're using hot coffee, a blender or milk frother keeps it from clumping.</p>

    <h2>"But I Also Eat Eggs in the Morning"</h2>

    <p>Good. Two large eggs give you about 12g of protein and roughly 1g of leucine. Still short of the threshold on their own — which is why the "2 eggs is enough" idea is one of the most common mistakes men over 40 make.</p>

    <p>Two eggs plus collagen? Still probably short. Two eggs plus whey? Now you're in range. The math matters more after 40 than it ever did before.</p>

    <h2>What Your Morning Actually Needs to Look Like</h2>

    <p>The research-backed target for men over 40 is <strong>25–40g of protein per meal</strong>, with particular emphasis on the morning window and post-training meals. Here's how common morning routines actually stack up:</p>

