      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can I mix collagen and whey together in coffee?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Collagen peptides dissolve well in hot coffee. For whey, cold brew or a blender works better to avoid clumping. Many men mix both into a morning shake alongside their coffee rather than directly in it.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is collagen a waste of money if it doesn't build muscle?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">No. Collagen supports joints, tendons, skin, and gut lining — all relevant for men over 40 who train. It just has a different job than whey. The right approach is using both, not replacing one with the other.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What kind of whey is best for men over 40?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Whey isolate is the cleanest option — higher protein percentage, lower lactose, easier on digestion. Look for at least 20–25g protein per serving and minimal additives.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Does the timing of protein in the morning matter?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. The morning window after an overnight fast is when your body is most primed to use a leucine signal for muscle protein synthesis. Getting 25–40g within the first hour or two of waking is one of the highest-leverage habits for men trying to maintain muscle after 40.</div>
      </div>
